It appears that the challenges in this area have begun to emerge. Due to the FAA's stance on certain medications, I may find it difficult to obtain a medical certification.
This is not impossible, but it would require a significant amount of time and additional effort.
Although this is a bit disheartening, it's just another problem that needs to be solved, and it appears that it can indeed be solved for now. However, it will require a significant amount of time and money.
If you want to know what challenges I will be facing next:
If you are taking medication for ADHD, you can definitely forget about getting a medical certification.
If you're watching the video of my first flight on YouTube, you'll see that I was taking medication for ADHD at the time.
If I ever have the chance to customize an aircraft's tail number, it must be a variation of N1337_, where _ represents any available alphabetic character.
Of course, the sun will still rise as usual when I'm not around, haha. What a downer.
I'm looking forward to flying again, but this unfavorable weather is really not cooperating.
